commits.message:
Build dependencies in integrations-core with omnibus

The output of the build is at this point a tar.gz with the resolved
requirements and a folder with the wheels, and we only include those
deps that don't require special treatment.

Add the ability to assert the `external_tags` when running tests

### Motivation
<!-- What inspired you to submit this pull request? -->

The Platform integrations team uses them and would like to have a way to assert them without mocking the function.

comment.body:
Oh, I focused on the "unreleased" part and didn't see the big picture question, sorry.

I'm looking into this. Options so far:

1. add `no-changelog` to new integration PRs, keep changelogs as they are.
2. somehow make the "new integration template" support both our workflow and that of external contributors.
3. manually adjust the changelog coming from the template to fit our new system (changelog gets generated when we release).
